    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix pack_config_request() num_tlv counting issue\n\n### Summary\nThe `pack_config_request()` function in nfapi_p5.c was not properly counting the number of valid TLVs before packing, causing mismatch between the reported count and actual packed TLVs. This led to unpacking errors on the receiving end.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p5.c`: Added logic to count valid TLVs by checking if each TLV's tag matches the expected value, then updating `pNfapiMsg->num_tlv` with this count before pushing it\n- Also fixed the same issue in `pack_nr_config_request()` for consistency\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `pack_config_request()` with partially populated TLVs, the function would push an incorrect `num_tlv` value that didn't match the actual number of TLVs that were packed (since `pack_tlv` only packs TLVs with valid tags). This caused the receiving end to either read garbage data or miss TLVs entirely when unpacking.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Create a `nfapi_config_request_t` structure\n2. Set only a subset of TLVs with proper tag values\n3. Call `pack_config_request()` \n4. Observe that `num_tlv` pushed doesn't match actual packed TLVs\n5. On unpacking side, incorrect number of TLVs are processed\n\nThe fix ensures that `num_tlv` accurately reflects the number of TLVs that will actually be packed by checking each TLV's tag before incrementing the count.\n"
}